<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>HealthTrack - About</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>HealthTrack</h1>
      <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <% if (currentUserId) { %>
          <a href="/activities/my">My Activities</a>
          <a href="/activities/add">Add Activity</a>
          <a href="/search">Search</a>
          <a href="/stats">Stats</a>
          <a href="/users/logout">Logout (<%= currentUsername %>)</a>
        <% } else { %>
          <a href="/users/register">Register</a>
          <a href="/users/login">Login</a>
        <% } %>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <h2>About HealthTrack</h2>
      <p>
        HealthTrack is a health and fitness tracking application built as part of the
        Dynamic Web Applications module. It demonstrates:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Node.js, Express, EJS templating</li>
        <li>MySQL data storage</li>
        <li>User registration, login and password hashing</li>
        <li>Form handling, validation and sanitisation</li>
        <li>Search and reporting features</li>
        <li>A JSON API endpoint for activities</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The focus of the project is on demonstrating backend and database skills
        rather than visual design.
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
